				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, I am glad they told us about the code in the new expansion.  Just one more Verant product I won't be buying. <BR>
<BR>
And all you thoughtless morons who keep crying &quot;Farmers Farmers!!&quot;, obviously you have never played the game at all. The entire game is NOTHING BUT FARMING!! You have to farm pelts for tailoring, countless components for spell research, bonechips for pets, various items for factions, etc etc etc.<BR>
 <BR>
This brings to mind when I set up my pet in HP to kill orcs, and everyone in the zone flipped friggin out when my pet easily slaughtered the orcs. All the orcs. And I refused to yeild to any of the lower levels. I was there first, I had the camp, and I didn't move at all. Yes, they petitioned, and a GM came, and I told her the same thing. If I had came and another group had the camp, she wouldn't let me in there, so why should I let them in because things were reversed?? I ended both of thier arguments by simply saying to the group wanting the camp, and the GM present there, &quot;OK, you can have the camp. Provided the GM puts into my inventory all the ringmail I need. (Ringmail is a burnable component for spell research.) Gee, suddenly the GM saw my point exactly, as I told her it wqas not my idea, but VERANTS to stay there and farm. If you don't want me to farm, take out the components required for spell research. The GM saw my point, and told the group to leave me alone and let me have the camp till I wished to go. I was collecting ringmail pieces, a reqiured component, that yes, a high level such as myself had to have. Isn't that farming?? <BR>
<BR>
Oh well, I'm just another of the countless people who WILL NOT be buying the new expansion. Verant -- If you don't want farming, stop setting up your game to require it.
				</font>
			</td>

